title: Chipmaker AMD beats estimates for third-quarter revenue - Yahoo Finance
description: (Reuters) -Advanced Micro Devices on Tuesday forecast fourth-quarter revenue just shy of estimates as supply chain constraints hamper its ability to meet strong demand for AI chips, while the PC market grows more slowly than some investors expected.  Demand for AI chips from big technology companies including Microsoft and Meta has been rising much faster than their supply from AMD and larger rival Nvidia, limiting the chip companies' ability to tap the order surge.  Revenue in its data center business, which includes AI chips, surged 122% to $3.5 billion, topping estimates.
